    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This collection contains issues of B.A.N.G. Notes: The Newsletter of the Brooklyn Anti-Nuclear Group, 1981-1986. The collection includes the first and last issues, but is an incomplete run with some duplicates. The content of these newsletters includes information about nuclear disarmament and anti-nuclear power campaigns, as well as notices and articles about related movements, such as the anti-draft movement and the American Indian Movement, especially related to land sovereignty issues. B.A.N.G. Notes also published poems, letters, opinion pieces, and cartoons.</field>
    <field name="bioghist_teim">The Brooklyn Anti-Nuclear Group (BANG) formed in 1978 as an anti-nuclear power, anti-nuclear weapons, anti-racist, anti-sexist, anti-exploitation group.</field>
    <field name="bioghist_teim">The first B.A.N.G. Notes newsletter was released in January 1981 to notify people of BANG's rate withholding campaign against Con Edison's rate increases after a leak at the Indian Point nuclear power plant, and other demonstrations and events. The newsletter was initially sent to rate withholders, left in stores around Brooklyn, and accepted donations to contribute to publication and distribution costs. The last issue was released in early 1986.</field>
    <field name="acqinfo_teim">Gift of Jennifer Hoyer on behalf of the Interference Archive, 2019.</field>
    <field name="custodhist_teim">These newsletters were originally given to Interference Archive as part of a larger collection by Bob McGlynn, date unknown.</field>
    <field name="phystech_teim">The majority of the materials in this collection are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please contact cbhreference@bklynlibrary.org at least two weeks prior to research visit.</field>
    <field name="phystech_teim">If digital surrogates exist, they should be used in place of the originals whenever possible.</field>
